transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Mr. Keeton?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Mr. Keeton, so I did exactly what you wanted, but as a veteran, I take a lot of pride and

Speaker 2: honor in my work, so I did three things.

Speaker 1: The first thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly shipments, and the second

Speaker 2: thing I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly refills, and the third thing I did

Speaker 1: is I put a stop to any and all monthly charges, and I paused your prescription, I set it up

Speaker 2: so when you do decide to need it, you just click a button or you call me.

Speaker 1: My extension is 00370, and my name is J.T. Goodrich, bud, so you're all good to go instead,

Speaker 2: bud, and thanks for calling in, and thanks for allowing us to be of service, right, bud?

Speaker 1: Alrighty, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 1: Is that a parrot in the background, too?

Speaker 2: I grew up with macaws.

Speaker 1: Like what now?

Speaker 2: That noise, was that a parrot, like a macaw, an Amazon macaw?

Speaker 1: I think it might be my dog.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounded like a little macaw.

Speaker 1: Hey, squeaking, a squeaking little ball.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, very well.

Speaker 1: Well, you guys have fun, okay, and stay warm over there because it's burly cold right now,

Speaker 2: you're going to freeze your tail off, all right?

Speaker 1: I know it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it's getting cold.

Speaker 1: You take care.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Be safe.

Speaker 2: You take care, Mr. Quinton.

Speaker 1: Adios.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
